Full service (go build ./...)
  The full binary additionally links jackc/pgx (PostgreSQL driver), which depends on
  golang.org/x/{sync,text,crypto}. The sandbox network does not reach the Go module
  proxy / golang.org; routing those through the github.com/golang mirror instead pins
  versions whose go.mod now requires Go >= 1.24, while this sandbox has Go 1.22.2.
  The full-service link was therefore not exercised on Linux. This is a sandbox
  network/toolchain limitation, not a code issue.

Cross-environment summary for the Go component
  Windows host (Go 1.26): full Storage Provider builds and runs (Postgres-backed),
                          exercised end-to-end via the setup script.
  Linux  (Go 1.22.2):     the assigned internal/crypto package builds and its full
